Prime Minister David Cameron of the United Kingdom will be visiting the White House on May 13, 2013. The purpose of the visit is to emphasize the importance of the U.S.-UK relationship and to discuss shared global and regional security concerns, such as Syria, trade and economic cooperation, countering terrorism, and priorities for the upcoming G-8 Summit in Northern Ireland. The visit highlights the special relationship between the two countries and the strategic importance of collaborating on global challenges. President Obama also mentions his upcoming visit to Northern Ireland in June for the G-8 Summit, which will be hosted by Prime Minister Cameron.